![Cushion vs radiant cut diamond price head-to-head infographic: G-VS1 to D-VVS1 comparison at 1ct showing cushion saves 15-30% at G-F-E colour tiers](/images/cushion-vs-radiant-price-comparison.avif)

**Reading the price table.** At G-VS1 Ideal, the cushion saves approximately $400 over an equivalent radiant. At E-VS1 Ideal, the saving widens significantly — the radiant's E-tier pricing is dramatically higher than cushion modified brilliant at the same colour tier. At D-VVS1 Ideal, the gap inverts: the radiant is fractionally cheaper at 1ct. The practical takeaway: cushion offers better value at the G-F-E colour tier; radiant is competitive only at the top D tier.

**Why the price gap exists.** Cushion modified brilliants are more abundant in supply than radiant cuts at the same quality tier — Blue Nile's cushion inventory outnumbers its radiant inventory at any given quality bracket. Higher supply pushes cushion pricing down relative to radiant. The radiant's relative scarcity in the G-F-E colour range at Ideal cut creates the visible pricing gap in the middle tier rows.

